      "span_text": "In aged skin, fibroblasts adjacent to fragmented collagen are less stretched, and by inference have lower mechanical tension.  85 Our results in collagen lattices demonstrate that collagen fragmentation causes loss of stretch, which results in increased levels of oxidants."
